My initial trial will be scaled down from the model described above, but my goal remains to develop a grading system that encourages risk-taking, improves motivation, cultivates collaboration and fosters creativity.

**(d) A final account of all sources and kinds of salary support, other than the sabbatical leave stipend, with a description of the sabbaticant’s activity, if any, necessary to receive each such type of fund.**

During my sabbatical leave, I did not request financial support from the College other than my paid sabbatical leave. Research materials for my sabbatical were acquired via interlibrary loans or were purchased by myself. Activities described in section (a) of this report (conferences, colloquia, workshops and travel) were supported by the Learning Games Network and LGN partnerships with MIT. 

I have been hired by LGN to continue on the Xenos-ISLE Project as curriculum and game designer for approximately 20 hours per week from May 1, 2012 to August 31, 2012 and as pre-pilot workshop facilitator for approximately 8 hours per week from September 1, 2012 to December 31, 2012. 

